# Git Integration — Advanced Patterns

## Per-Symbol Git History

nyne scopes git operations to symbol line ranges, filtering out unrelated commits.

### Symbol-scoped log

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/LOG.md
```

Shows only commits that modified lines within `Foo`'s range. More precise than
`git log -L` because nyne tracks symbol boundaries through renames and refactors.

### Symbol-scoped blame

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/BLAME.md         # full symbol blame
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/BLAME.md:5-10    # lines 5-10 within the symbol
```

Line numbers are relative to the symbol, not the file.

## File-Level Git

### Commit log with slicing

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md           # full log
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md:-10       # last 10 commits
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md:5-15      # commits 5-15
```

The `:M-N` range syntax is a generic nyne pattern. Negative offsets count from the end.

### Blame with line ranges

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/BLAME.md            # full file blame
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/BLAME.md:42-55      # blame for specific lines
```

### Contributors

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/CONTRIBUTORS.md     # ranked by line ownership
cat dir@/git/CONTRIBUTORS.md         # aggregated across directory
```

### Uncommitted changes

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/diff/HEAD.diff          # uncommitted changes for this file
cat dir@/diff/HEAD.diff              # uncommitted changes across directory
```

## Repository-Level Git

```sh
cat @/git/STATUS.md            # working tree status, staged changes
ls @/git/branches/             # branch listing
ls @/git/tags/                 # tag listing
```

### Branch operations

```sh
# Rename a branch
mv @/git/branches/old-name @/git/branches/new-name
# → executes git branch -m
```

## Git Notes

```sh
cat file.{{ ext }}@/git/NOTES.md         # git notes for commits touching this file
cat dir@/git/NOTES.md             # git notes aggregated across directory
```
